Italy, just east of the Roman Forum and is the largest ancient amphitheatre ever built,
and is still the largest standing amphitheater in the world today, despite its age. Construction
began under the emperor Vespasian in 72 and was completed in AD 80 under his
successor and heir, Titus . Further modifications were made during the reign of Domitian .
